page.title: 05Canal-Wildlife Welshampton
page.content: There's alot of wildlife in and around the canal.The fish do well in the canal but sometimes there is pollution which kills the fish.There are various types of fish in the canal,one of the most common is the stickleback but there is also dace,perch,pike,eels,gugeon,ruffe, roach,Millers Thumb or Bullhead,chub and bream.There are quite a few people that come to fish in the canal.There are some water birds that go to the canal aswell.These are some of them mallard,moorhen,swan and heron.There are not many birds that go on the canal because alot of boats go there and it disturbs the birds.There are water voles which make their nest in the side of the canal.We also get damsel flies there.
